{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_67","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\"","aggregated_output":"Issue: obsolete GO:0008785 alkyl hydroperoxide reductase activity\n\nThis task does not add or revise any logical definitions or DOSDP-driven compositional terms. The relevant pattern is GO obsoletion with direct replacement in the catalytic activity branch.\n\nRelevant local precedent:\n\n* GO:0102040 obsolete fumarate reductase (menaquinone)\n    - Obsoleted molecular function term in the catalytic activity branch.\n    - Keeps only provenance/obsoletion metadata and uses `replaced_by` for the surviving active term.\n\n* GO:0015039 obsolete NADPH-adrenodoxin reductase activity\n    - Direct-replacement obsoletion where the old term was equivalent to a broader surviving activity term.\n    - Comment explains the equivalence rationale.\n\nImplications for this issue:\n\n* GO:0008785 should retain namespace, original definition provenance, tracker items, and gain an obsoletion reason plus `replaced_by: GO:0102039`.\n* No `is_a`, `relationship`, `intersection_of`, or synonyms should remain on the obsolete term.\n* GO-internal references to GO:0008785 must be removed or rewired.\n* For `GO:0009321 alkyl hydroperoxide reductase complex`, the `See also` comment should point to the active surviving molecular function term `GO:0102039 NADH-dependent peroxiredoxin activity`.\n* The `GO:0070937` comment mentioning GO:0008785 is stray and should be removed rather than rewired, because the term is unrelated to peroxiredoxin activity.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
